{
  "stem": "10572.5",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 11.7,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 19,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 4 SECONDS] You know, in these kind of manifestations of decency among-- also kept us-- kept us going.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "No, no, no, no, no.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, they were really-- the-- the average citizen I think was frightened by all this.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And again, as an indication and as a symbol of some of the things that happened, there was a man and a woman who lived in a little house who were in charge of the parks, a park worker, [NON-ENGLISH] Heineke.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And one day-- and my parents couldn't go to the grocery anymore to buy butter.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And one day, there was at night, there was the doorbell rang.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And my mother went to the door.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "There was nobody there.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "But there was a package-- [PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] --with a pound of butter.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "[CRYING] So-- which is probably one of the reasons that when people judge and condemn people in general terms and say 'the Germans' or 'the Jews,' that is an injustice that I have learned through this whole period should not exist.",
      "word_count": 41
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And then, because of what had happened during Kristallnacht, some positive forces came into effect.",
      "word_count": 15
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we heard about it, that the Archbishop of Canterbury, Cosmo Long, had been convinced by a classmate of his from Goettingen University, Professor James Franck, Nobel Prize winner, who had convinced him in order to save 5,000 young Jews to convince the British government to start a camp.",
      "word_count": 49
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 20,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And the Lord Kitchener Camp came into existence.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And that was in England.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was on the southeast coast of England near Margate and Ramsgate, near Dover, near Canterbury, near Foxton.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I was one of the lucky ones.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 21,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "My brother-in-law and my sister left Germany on the 23rd of June, 1939, eight weeks before outbreak of the war, and went to England.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 22,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Pardon me?",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "Horrible.",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "It was horrible for both of us because we didn't know.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "After Buchenwald, we had no illusions.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And-- but the only justification that I felt was that I could work more effectively from England for their immigration.",
      "word_count": 20
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "And we went into this camp, which was a prisoner of war camp during the First World War, a very primitive, run-down camp, which we rebuilt.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And we lived very primitively on porridge and cabbage in this camp with a potbelly stove in the middle of the barrack.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "But for us, it was paradise.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "This was it.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "This was freedom.",
      "word_count": 3
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "And we lived in a civilized society among decent people.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "And we didn't have to apologize.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "And then the war broke out.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 23,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "And then--",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "1st of September '39 when Hitler invaded Poland, [NON-ENGLISH].",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And England lived up to their promise and declared war.",
      "word_count": 10
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And I had gone on the 25th of August, a week before the war broke out.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 24,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "I had gone with the signatures of 25 of my buddies in my barrack to the Bloomsbury House in London to volunteer for the British Army.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "And the British were so unbelievable.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They had no idea what was going on.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "And they looked at me like I was nuts.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "You know, why do you want to-- want to go with the British Army?",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 25,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "There is no war.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I said, there will be.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "No, no, don't worry about it.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "England has never lost a war.",
      "word_count": 6
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "And they didn't want us.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Later on, the majority of the 5,000 in this camp became part of the British forces and furnished very, very valuable-- many of them got into the intelligence service.",
      "word_count": 29
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 26,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "And--",
      "word_count": 1
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "I-- I left-- I left-- I finally got my invitation to come to the American embassy in London to get my immigration visa to the United States.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And I couldn't-- couldn't fathom that, you know.",
      "word_count": 8
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "This was-- and it was 'the' day' for me.",
      "word_count": 9
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "It was 'the' door.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "I said in my story, I walked through many, many doors to come to this point.",
      "word_count": 16
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "But this was 'the' door.",
      "word_count": 5
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 27,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And I hoped and prayed that I would meet the conditions or the things that were necessary to meet the qualifications of the American consulate.",
      "word_count": 25
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "They left.",
      "word_count": 2
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "They left much later.",
      "word_count": 4
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 28,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "I came to America first.",
      "word_count": 5
    }
  ],
